16/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Sixteen Turkish nationals were arrested in Pakistan on Saturday (August 15th) for suspected ties to the al-Qaeda terrorist organisation. 
NTV reports that the Turkish nationals were detained along with 14 Azeri citizens when their bus was stopped for inspections in Quetta, Balochistan. 
Five women and four children were among the Turkish detainees. 
(NTV, APA - 15/08/09)
